    <description>&lt;p&gt;Joyce Warrington the Director of HVAC Brand Marketing at Ingersoll Rand and and Lindsay Rose the Marketing representative join Craig on the floor of CES to discuss quality products, services and solutions include mechanical and electronic locks, heating and air conditioning systems, indoor air quality solutions, advanced controls, portable security systems and remote home management that deliver safety, comfort and efficiency to homeowners throughout North America.  With Nexia Home Intelligence is a new smart home automation system that homeowners can manage from wherever they are in the world to help bring safety, comfort and efficiency together under one roof. It leverages advanced technologies of trusted home industry leaders &amp;mdash; Trane and Schlage &amp;mdash; to make everything in your home speak one simple language. Nexia Home Intelligence is rooted in the real-world needs of everyday households, it supports today&apos;s mobile lifestyles and it allows people to remotely manage features and functions of their home via any Web-enabled computer and most smart phones.  Immediately following this interview Craig will be joined by Sarah Tomlinson the Marketing &amp;#38; Customer Relations Coordinator at iDevices.  iDevices develops App-enabled products that incorporate wireless connectivity to Apple devices. They discuss the iShower a water resistant, Bluetooth enabled speaker that plays music directly from your Apple and Android devices.  The iShower will mount in your shower or can be taken to the beach or pool. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
